I just wanted to learn the reason for this change. pid_t is a typedef for int according to the following grep output, but it would be better to keep this as pid_t, I think.


$ git grep 'typedef.*__kernel_pid_t' include/
include/linux/types.h:typedef __kernel_pid_t            pid_t;
include/uapi/asm-generic/posix_types.h:typedef int      __kernel_pid_t;


Note: Service manager source code in cgcs-root/stx/ha/service-mgmt/sm/src/sm_process_death.c has a copy of this code, and sm fails to build due to a duplicate struct declaration error. The duplicate declaration error is unrelated to this question; I noticed this change while resolving that issue.

